The eliciting by promiſes of indemnity, and the publick faith interpoſed for that effect voluntary confeſſions of ſome as of Mr. Iames Mitchill &c. and then not only retracting, and diſſowning the promiſe & condition upon Oath, in face of the juſtice court, but further witneſſing the confeſſion to the poor mans condemnation: not with ſtanding the bookes of council containing the aforſaid indemnity were produced and laid open before and at the very time of their ſwearing; Lyke as of Late after moſt cruel and exquiſit tortures practiſed upon Mr. Spens & Mr. Carſtairs, and a full & ample promiſe there after made them with an act upon it, that neither they nor their evidence should ever be made uſe of to their or to any other mens hurt; they never the leſs cauſe produce and do ſuſt
                     •
